<br>
 The dark and hate-filled part of her wanted to strike him dead with her very own magiks, yet death seemed either too merciful, or too severe. And through it all, the nurturing part of her held on to a small amount of hope for his dark salvation. Now, after 3 days of waiting, he was before her, near death, begging for the forgiveness of the family. <br>
<br>
She stood with her arms folded in front of her chest, her signature grin decorating her indigo face. <br>
<br>
“Well, well...here we are..” she purred. “ I must say, Talastius...you are quite the pitiful sight. Once a strong and noble knight, now stripped of all power, brought to this pathetic mess before me. It’s all quite sad”. <br>
<br>
Cielo walked over and stood directly in front of the battered ex-knight and looked down at him, her face now wearing a scowl.<br>
<br>
“Some in this very room think you unfit for redemption in any form. I would tend to agree with them, although what I have in mind will cause such incredible pain, death would be a gift from the gods“. Cielo knelt down and lifted his chin, forcing his eyes to meet hers and spoke softly to him. “So, it’s forgiveness you seek, hmmm? It shant come to you easily. You have upset us for the very last time, Talastius. You must prove your worth once again. Will you accept and endure all I have in store for you?” Cielo raised an eyebrow at him.<br>
<br>
Talastius’s head nodded weakly in agreement, and Cielo removed her hand from his chin, letting his head drop to his chest and turned to Grogo.<br>
<br>
“Grogo, take this poor excuse for a teir’dal to his former chamber, please” Grogo immediately lifted the knight into his powerful arms. “Vyany and Fajon, please accompany Grogo to Talastius’s chamber. I will need you to heal him to full capacity. Brynvin, prepare the purification ritual as we have planned. It shall begin tomorrow morn.”<br>
<br>
With that everyone went to work preparing for the proceedings the following morning.<br>
