&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The sounds of boots sternly tapping against the stone floor and the almost military sound of moving armor as well as swishing robes filled the torchlit hallway as the small procession snaked its way to the room where Talastius was being kept.  Grogo held a torch out before him to light their way, the hall barely large enough to contain the ogre's fearful frame.  Behind him, Cielo walked silently, the shadows were almost darker than the frown she wore on her smooth indigo face that even Vermelo, who walked softly by her side, had not been able to lighten. Behind them, in rows of two, were Brynvin and Vyany, and then Fajon and Cook.  The rest of the Nightmare waited in the bowels of Prime Keep, in the freshly refurbished chapel.<br>
<br>
