<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp A guard at Talastius's door unlocked it, sending it open with a mournful creak.  Light poured in from the hallway onto the lowly inhabitant of the room who sat wearily up from his cot, a hand shielding his eyes and face.  There was something different about him...<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Bring him,&quot; Brynvin's voice cut through the silence like a cold steel blade.  Obediently, the two guards marched into the room and picked Talastius up, each gripping an arm and dragging him out into the hallway.  Hair that was once like freshly fallen snow now hung limply and filth-drenched in the errant Teir`Dal's shadowed face.  Slowly, Brynvin stepped forward and slipped a cool finger under Talastius's chin, lifting his face into the light, exposing his freshly marred features.  Her voice caught for a moment in her throat in surprise before a cruel grin spread across her crimson lips.  Softly, she stepped back and let his head droop forward again.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Well, he needs a bath... to say the least.  Talastius, strip.  If you cannot, it will be done for you,&quot; she ordered sternly.  With a nod to the guards by Cielo, Talastius's arms were released and he did as he was bade, a meager pile of cloth armor at the floor beside him mere moments later.  Grogo carefully held up a simple black robe and then handed it out toward Talastius.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Wear dis,&quot; the ogre instructed.  With a nod, Talastius took the robe and slipped it around his wrecked blue body.  As he began to tie it shut, Brynvin spoke up once again, her gaze locked on one item he had not taken off.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;That <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>thing</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> around your neck, remove it.&quot;  For the first time since his disfigurement, Talastius looked directly at someone, glaring at Brynvin, and then he spoke.  His voice was as cool and plain as his answer.<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;No.&quot;<br>
<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;No?&quot;  The priestess glanced back at Cielo for a moment and her eyes narrowed as she returned her gaze to him, burning with the same suspicion the others must have been feeling as well.  &quot;You <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> remove it, or it <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be removed for you.&quot;  With reluctance, Talastius reached up and untied the pouch that rested around his neck, gripping it tightly there for a moment.<br>
