<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>~~~~The Ritual~~~~</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<br>
The procession slowly made it's way down the ancient stone steps that spiraled deep into the bowels of Prime Keep. Eerie torchlight filled the narrow tunnel, their cloaked bodies throwing ominous shadows on the walls. Only footsteps could be heard echoing through the stairwell. When they reached the last step, the hall opened up into a large room. <br>
<br>
The alter, a chiseled stone slab set at a slight angle, had been erected in the center of the cavernous temple and now stood amidst tiers of glowing candles that created a luminous circle around it. Immediately to the right of the alter was an ornate table where the amassment of the items and tools to be used in the ritual had been laid out, a red silken cloth hiding them from sight. On two sides of the sacred alter, the balance of the Nightmare sat in sturdy pues crafted from the oldest, darkest trees of the Nektulos forest and there they waited.<br>
<br>
Brynvin entered first, closely followed by the two hulking guards and their condemned captive. With a nod to the guards, she motioned toward the alter. Promptly, the guards stepped forward and lead Talastius under the archway of towering candles to stand before the stone slab, facing away from it. The procession quietly spilled into the room behind them. Vyany and Fajon both took a place at Talastius's side as the guards moved away to stand outside the ring of candles, still keeping a stern and watchful eye on their charge. Cook, Grogo, Vermelo and Cielo moved to stand outside the the glowing barrier and observe, none of them yet allowed within the candlelit circle.<br>
<br>
Once assembled, Vyany and Fajon moved in unison, each taking hold of Talastius's robe and sliding it back from his shoulders until he stood bare before the assembly. Folding the robe neatly, Fajon turned and placed it on the table who's freshly exposed contents now gleamed and glimmered under the twinkling of candles. Brynvin removed three cloths from the table, handing one each to Vyany and Fajon and retaining one for herself. The trio then saturated their cloths with saltwater from a large marble bowl atop the table and wordlessly began to scrub away at the grimy indigo skin of the knight.<br>
<br>
When every inch of his body had been cleansed to the priests' satisfaction, they each stepped back from Talastius and pointed to the cold stone slab that awaited him. He showed no resistance to their wish for him to lie down. As he began to recline, moistened tangles of hair fell back from his face, revealing the wrecked features beneath to the onlookers. Cielo closed her eyes tightly and a deep sigh escaped her violet lips. Vermelo, seeing her distress, grasped her hand firmly, trying to comfort her as much as he could. Reluctantly, Cielo turned from the alter as Cook and Vermlo stepped into the circle. Not noticing her delicate hands clenching into rock hard fists, she stiffly headed to her seat in the front pue, where Frizzled and Spehk had been sitting in a reverent silence.<br>
<br>
The time of purification had arrived.<br>
<br>
Before taking their places around the alter each cleric took a ceremonial rune in hand and marked Talastius's body where the incisions would be made and then set them back upon the table, where both Vyany and Fajon each retrieved a  ceremonial dagger.<br>
<br>
Brynvin took her place at the head of the alter, spreading her arms up high above her, her palms angled toward the ceiling. Vyany stepped to the right side of the alter, Fajon to the left, and each, firmly gripping the hilt of their daggers in both hands, held them aloft with their gleaming points reaching toward the darkness above. Simultaneously, the three began chanting a prayer in Elder Teir`Dal.<br>
<br>
Vyany began her call to Innoruuk. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Father Innoruuk, Prince of Hate, hear me...<br>
<br>
Lend me your power this day,<br>
<br>
so I may cleanse this knight,<br>
<br>
making him worthy again to serve you as an instrument of hatred.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
<br>
As Vyany continued her chant, Fajon began his prayer to the Goddess Terris Thule. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Lady Terris-Thule, Goddess of Nightmares. hear me...<br>
<br>
Lend me your power this day,<br>
<br>
so I may cleanse this knight,<br>
<br>
making him once again worthy to serve you with the creation of nightmares.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
Vyany and Fajon continued their chants as Brynvin began her call to her own god.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Ancient god, Spirit of Blood, hear me... <br>
<br>
Lend me your power this day,<br>
<br>
so I may clense and purify the blood of this weakened knight,<br>
<br>
making him once against worthy of his gods, House and race.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
<br>
Their voices intermingled in a haunting chorus that filled the temple. As they chanted faster and faster, an intense energy could be felt by all within the room. Brynvin lowered her arms somewhat, stretching her palms out to meet the daggers of Vyany and Fajon that were slowly lowering as well. The two tips touched together just above Brynvin's open palms, creating a fierce explosion of light as the combined powers of their gods were channeled over him. A force, unseen, sprang from the apex of the energy and ripped through the knight's body, sending him into uncontrollable convulsions. The guards rushed forward into the circle to hold him down for the coming incisions.<br>
<br>
As they mutilated his battered body, his face contorted with a look of horrible pain. Tortured moans escaped his lips but he spoke no words. The blessed daggers were set back upon the table and Talastius's body was once again still. The guards releases their grip and stepped back from the alter. Blood flowed feely from the new wounds that were quickly cleaned with saltwater as his body had been. Talastius resolved not to wail, but the incredible pain in the already painful wounds was unbareable. His screams echoed in the temple, resonating in the ears of the onlookers. The bloody cloths were tossed back into the marble bowl, changing the water to a pale pink.<br>
<br>
Brynvin leaned down, her face near the fallen knight's right ear and spoke softly with contempt in her voice.<br>
<br>
&quot;Shall we stop, Talastius? Do you wish this to end? Say aye, so I may have the pleasure of killing you.&quot;<br>
<br>
Talastius gritted his teeth and narrowed his tear-filled eyes with resolve. <br>
<br>
&quot;I shall endure all that is in store for me. You shall have no such pleasure.&quot;<br>
<br>
An angered sigh escaped her lips as she stood back up to perform the blood purification.<br>
<br>
Cook stepped forward toward the alter and awaited Brynvin's cue. She slowly and carefully willed the blood out of the open wounds on Talastius's body into a large bowl. The knight felt the warmth leaving his body and his life fading away. The candles which once so brightly burned in his vision were now barely more than pinpricks of light, like the stars across a midnight sky. Before death could overtake him, though, she nodded to Cook, and with a touch of his hand, the powerful wizard had frozen the body of the knight to the point of suspended animation.<br>
<br>
With the power of her god coursing through her veins, the Blood Priestess set to purifying the very source of the outcast's life. She dipped her hands in the warm fluid contents of the bowl and filled her upturned palms. She closed her eyes, speaking a hushed incantation under her breath, and transferred the blood into another bowl. Again and again she took up fresh handfuls of his blood until there was not a single drop that she had not fortified. Casting a final spell on the basin of rejuvenated blood, filling the room with a brilliant scarlet glow, her words commanded the blood to rise up in streams from the bowl and back into the body through the same wounds from whence it had been drawn.<br>
<br>
When all of Talastius's blood was in his veins once again, Brynvin opened her eyes and again nodded to Cook. He touched the frigid body of the knight, this time with the heat of fire, and again the knight drew breath. With that, Cook stepped back from the alter to make way for Vermelo as the next step of purification arrived.<br>
<br>
It was time now for the purification of his mind. Vermelo stepped forward as Cook had and called upon the radiance of Innoruuk to help him in his task. He placed his hand on Talastius's forehead and the knight's eyes began to widen. The enchanter spoke a short incantation, to which a screech tore from Talastius's lip as he threw his head back, his mind shattered by Chaotic Feedback. In the next moment, Talastius stared blankly up toward the ceiling, a puddle of drool pooling near his head. His mind lay in a broken ruin, functioning only at the most basic level. It was up to the masterful enchanter to rebuild the mind of his kinsman. Lightly, he placed both hands on the knight's head. Vermelo closed his eyes tightly and began to chant, faster and faster as he went on. He imbued the knight's mind with hatred and a new order as his powers reconstructed the broken mind, finally giving him clarity of mind to bring his senses back to him. As Talastius became aware of his surroundings, Vermelo stepped back.<br>
<br>
Talastius looked about the room, confusion and terror upon his indigo face. Weakly, he looked down at the still open and bleeding wounds decorating his body and then vaguely understood why he was there. But the ritual was not quite over. Lastly, the scars were to be set. All of the knight's wounds, old and new, were packed with clay to keep the skin from repairing itself, leaving it permanently disfigured, to serve as a reminder of his shameful transgressions each time he looked upon himself. <br>
<br>
The end had come.<br>
<br>
As Brynvin methodically extinguished the candles to close the cermemony, Fajon and Vyany began to heal Talastius. Grogo approached the alter and stood next to his comrade, awaitng the cue to escort the kngiht to his chamber. When the healing was complete, Grogo placed his large right arm under the new knight's back and helped him to the floor. As Talastius was lead out, the procession reconvened and traveled back up the stairwell to the Keep.<br>
